        <div type="letter">
            <div type="text">
                <opener>
                    <salute>My dear D<hi rend="superscript">r</hi>. W.—</salute>
                </opener>
                <div type="transcription">
                     
<p>As experience in an Examination, of the same nature, as those to be ultimately passed, must be very useful to any young man, in curing him from nervousness &amp; as a stimulus to exertion, I wish my son L. to try for W. this winter.<ref target="#foot.f2"/> From what I gather, he has <hi rend="underline">small</hi>  chance of success, but he assures me that he will not feel discouraged by failure.—<ref target="#foot.f3"/></p>
<p>I may take this opportunity of informing you that for various considerations, I wish to send H. after Xmas to a private Tutor.<ref target="#foot.f4"/> But I hope that you will not suppose that I feel dissatisfied with Clapham. On the contrary I always rejoice that my 4 sons have been under D<hi rend="superscript">r</hi>. P &amp; your care;<ref target="#foot.f5"/> &amp; I cordially thank you for your <hi rend="italic">[</hi>wonderful<hi rend="italic">]</hi> K.<ref target="#foot.f6"/> to them &amp; myself—</p>
<p>Believe me my dear D<hi rend="superscript">r</hi>. W | Yours very f. | C. D</p>
<p>P.S. My son H. has a strong desire to make greater progress in Math; therefore if you can assist him in this respect. I sh<hi rend="superscript">d</hi>. feel much obliged.—<ref target="#foot.f7"/></p> 
                </div>
            </div>
            <div type="tnotes">
